
TY  - JOUR
T1  - Under Threat: Responses to and the Consequences of Threats to Individuals' Identities
AU  - Petriglieri, Jennifer Louise
Y1  - 2011/10/01
PY  - 2011
DA  - 2011/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2009.0087
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2009.0087
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 641
EP  - 662
VL  - 36
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - I review and reconceptualize identity threat, defining it as an experience appraised as indicating potential harm to the value, meanings, or enactment of an identity. I also develop a theoretical model and propositions that generate insights into how individuals respond to identity threats originating from a range of sources. I use this theory to explore individual and organizational consequences of different identity threat responses and their implications for research on identity dynamics within organizations.
AB  - I review and reconceptualize identity threat, defining it as an experience appraised as indicating potential harm to the value, meanings, or enactment of an identity. I also develop a theoretical model and propositions that generate insights into how individuals respond to identity threats originating from a range of sources. I use this theory to explore individual and organizational consequences of different identity threat responses and their implications for research on identity dynamics within organizations.
