TY  - JOUR
T1  - Heterogeneous Motives and the Collective Creation of Value
AU  - Bridoux, Flore
AU  - Coeurderoy, Régis
AU  - Durand, Rodolphe
Y1  - 2011/10/01
PY  - 2011
DA  - 2011/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2009.0440
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2009.0440
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 711
EP  - 730
VL  - 36
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The collective creation of value has remained underexplored in management research. Drawing on social psychology and behavioral economics, we analyze the impact of the mix of employee motives to cooperate and compare the collective value generated by three motivational systems: individual monetary incentives, benevolent cooperation, and disciplined cooperation. Aligning the motivational system with the mix of motives in the workforce allows firms to foster cooperation and realize the value creation potential of their resources.
AB  - The collective creation of value has remained underexplored in management research. Drawing on social psychology and behavioral economics, we analyze the impact of the mix of employee motives to cooperate and compare the collective value generated by three motivational systems: individual monetary incentives, benevolent cooperation, and disciplined cooperation. Aligning the motivational system with the mix of motives in the workforce allows firms to foster cooperation and realize the value creation potential of their resources.
